{"id":438430,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gillo_Dorfles","text":"Gillo Dorfles (12 April 1910 \u2013 2 March 2018) was an Italian art critic, painter, and philosopher. Dorfles graduated in medicine, specializing in psychiatry. He was a professor in aesthetics at the University of Trieste, Milan and Cagliari. In 1948, he co-founded the Movimento per l'arte concreta (MAC) with artists Atanasio Soldati, Galliano Mazzon, Gianni Monnet, and Bruno Munari.\nDorfles was born on 12 April 1910 in Trieste. He died on 2 March 2018 at 107 years old in Milan.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Italians","surface_form":"Italian","offset":52},{"uri":"Art_critic","surface_form":"art critic","offset":60},{"uri":"Philosopher","surface_form":"philosopher","offset":85},{"uri":"Medicine","surface_form":"medicine","offset":119},{"uri":"Psychiatry","surface_form":"psychiatry","offset":145},{"uri":"Aesthetics","surface_form":"aesthetics","offset":179},{"uri":"University_of_Trieste","surface_form":"University of Trieste","offset":197},{"uri":"University_of_Milan","surface_form":"Milan","offset":220},{"uri":"University_of_Cagliari","surface_form":"Cagliari","offset":230},{"uri":"Movimento_per_l%27arte_concreta","surface_form":"Movimento per l'arte concreta","offset":267},{"uri":"Atanasio_Soldati","surface_form":"Atanasio Soldati","offset":316},{"uri":"Galliano_Mazzon","surface_form":"Galliano Mazzon","offset":334},{"uri":"Gianni_Monnet","surface_form":"Gianni Monnet","offset":351},{"uri":"Bruno_Munari","surface_form":"Bruno Munari","offset":370},{"uri":"Trieste","surface_form":"Trieste","offset":421},{"uri":"Milan","surface_form":"Milan","offset":474}]}